The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, May 26: Crisil today decided to reconstitute its board to reflect the new ownership structure after the acquisition of a majority stake by Standard amp; Poors. B. V. Bhargava will be the chairman and R. Ravimohan will be the managing director and chief executive officer. The reconstitution will be effective from July 21 after the annual general meeting of Crisil.

 Mumbai, May 26: Larsen amp; Toubro Ltd (L amp;T) has decided to sell its 50 per cent stake in the joint venture, L amp;T-Niro Ltd, to its partner Niro A/S of Denmark. L amp;T will also transfer the related business of building dairy plants to Niro. L amp;T refused to divulge the amount it will receive from the stake sale. 

 Mumbai, May 26: The Reserve Bank of India today said the gradually rising interest rates were unlikely to adversely affect commercial banks because of prospects of improvement in net interest income.

 Mumbai, May 26: Pantaloon Retail (India) will invest Rs 100 crore in the next three years to upgrade IT infrastructure in its lifestyle and retail businesses. It has tied up with SAP for the purpose.

 Calcutta, May 26: The government has formulated a rating scheme for the SSI sector and has tied up with Icra, Dun and Bradstreet, CARE, Crisil, Fitch and Onicra to provide the ratings.




